## A Glimpse Into Recent Recalls

On April 8, 2026, several food products faced recalls due to diverse safety issues. Notably, products such as dairy powders from Lone Star Dairy Products LLC were flagged for Salmonella contamination, a Class I recall indicating the most severe risk. Meanwhile, JFE Franchising's dumplings and party trays were recalled under Class II due to the presence of foreign objects (glass). Adding to these issues, popping boba teas from Pocas International Corp. were subject to Class III recalls for packaging integrity concerns.

## Allergens: The Silent Threat

Undeclared allergens continue to be a significant problem. The Maros Group LLC recalled prickly pear jelly and salad dressing due to undeclared milk and sulfites, both serious concerns for individuals with allergies. Similarly, HEYTEA USA faced a Class II recall for its coconut drink due to undeclared milk.

## The Numbers Behind the Recalls

This year alone, 302 recalls have occurred, with 84 being Class I, 193 Class II, and 25 Class III. Notable brands such as Moonlight Packing Corporation and Albertsons Companies LLC persist as the top repeat offenders with grades of "F" in food safety.

## A Call for Consumer Vigilance

While regulatory agencies and manufacturers are responsible for addressing these issues, consumers should remain vigilant, particularly regarding products they suspect may contain undeclared allergens or be poorly labeled. Awareness can prevent severe health risks.

## Worst Offenders

Moonlight Packing Corporation and Albertsons Companies LLC continue to dominate the list of repeat offenders, with over 11 recalls each this year alone, primarily Class I. CHETAK NEW YORK LLC leads the tally with a staggering 52 recalls.

## Recommendations to Brands

Food companies must enforce stricter quality controls to minimize recalls, particularly those arising from allergens, contamination, and foreign objects.

## Conclusion

The spike in recalls underscores the importance of food safety vigilance across production, labeling, and consumer education.
